Mafdet's Harbor Ledger House registers Priest practitioners under the oath obligation system, with specific provisions for public-benefit service.
Ward-network anchor points in harbor-adjacent structures require Strandline filing in addition to standard Temple Authority registration.
Priests who have registered as public-benefit providers and then restrict healing services to paying clients face oath-violation proceedings through the Shrine of the First Claw's enforcement mechanisms.
Maritime law creates specific situations: shipboard casualties involving spiritually contaminated wounds fall under harbor health jurisdiction as well as Temple Authority restoration protocol.

