---
Khenari death doctrine positions healing as an intervention in the natural departure process; the more significant tension is around ward-network maintenance: Khenari ward-networks in Midgaard's mortuary districts include wards against spiritual entities that Khenari theology classifies as incomplete descents, and maintenance protocols require death-ledger coordination to ensure wards target the correct classification of entity.
Khenari in Midgaard treat healing as completion support: sustaining the patient long enough for all nine descent stages to be properly prepared for when the time comes, rather than indefinitely deferring departure.
Khenari Priests in Midgaard are disproportionately represented in ward-network maintenance roles because their death-ledger precision translates directly to accurate ward-anchor classification, reducing the risk of ward systems that inadvertently exclude entities that should be protected against.

